parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CVT transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, or hesitate while accelerating, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or hesitates while accelerating
the transmission slips or fails to engage
the vehicle loses power
and the check engine light may or may not be illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake lights remain on
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
and the brake system warning light may be illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent loss of power can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate while driving, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power or hesitates while accelerating
the engine RPMs fluctuate
and the check engine light may or may not be illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage or failure.
symptoms: The cooling fan is loud or malfunctioning
the engine temperature gauge is in the red zone
and the check engine light may be illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hood latch can cause the hood to open while driving, obstructing the driver's view and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The hood bounces around while driving
especially on the highway or in windy conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling fan can cause engine damage, overheating, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The cooling fan makes a loud rattling or clunking noise
especially when the air conditioning or heating is turned on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning visor can obstruct the driver's view, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The visor fails to stay in place
dropping down and obstructing the driver's view.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air bag system can lead to the deployment of air bags in non-crash situations, failure to deploy in crash situations, or incorrect deployment, which can cause injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The air bag warning light is illuminated
the passenger air bag is turned off with an adult in the front passenger seat
the air bag deploys in non-crash situations
the air bag fails to deploy in crash situations
or the air bag deploys incorrectly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the OCS sensor can cause the passenger air bag to be turned off when an adult is in the front passenger seat, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The passenger air bag is turned off with an adult in the front passenger seat
the air bag warning light is illuminated
or the air bag deploys incorrectly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Takata Air Bag Recall Repair Delay
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing the Takata air bag recall can increase the risk of injury or fatality due to the faulty air bags.
symptoms: The part to repair the Takata air bag recall is unavailable
the manufacturer exceeds a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair
or the contact is unable to determine when the vehicle will be repaired.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CVT transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls or loses power
transmission slips or hesitates
unusual noises or vibrations from the transmission.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling fan can cause the engine to overheat, leading to costly repairs or even engine failure.
symptoms: Loud rattling or buzzing noise from the engine compartment
fan blades broken or loose
engine overheating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the acceleration system can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: Vehicle hesitates or stalls when accelerating
loss of power when accelerating
unusual noises or vibrations from the engine.
